   <body>
      <context>In the <uicontrol>FORECAST LIST</uicontrol> page, by default, all approved forecast records are displayed. You can  view the  forecast distribution   of  budget estimate items.</context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click <uicontrol>Projects</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>PROJECTS</uicontrol> list page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the list page, double-click the required project, and in the navigation pane, expand the project folder.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand <uicontrol>Budget Management</uicontrol>, and then click <uicontrol>Forecasts</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>FORECAST LIST</uicontrol> page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the list page, select the appropriate forecast record, and then click <uicontrol>View</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>GENERAL DETAILS</uicontrol> page is displayed.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <title>General Details Page</title>
                  <image href="../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Forecast_GnrlDetails.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>GENERAL DETAILS</uicontrol> page displays the following non-editable fields:<table colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <tgroup cols="2">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="30%"/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="70%"/>
                     <thead>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Field Name</entry>
                           <entry>Description</entry>
                        </row>
                     </thead>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry>ID</entry>
                           <entry>An identification number of the forecast. </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Description</entry>
                           <entry>The detailed description of the forecast.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Notes</entry>
                           <entry>The notes on the forecast.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Start Date</entry>
                           <entry>The   start date of the forecast.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>End Date</entry>
                           <entry>The   end date of the forecast.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Created On</entry>
                           <entry>The date on which the forecast is created.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Created By</entry>
                           <entry>The name of the user who created this forecast.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Approved On</entry>
                           <entry>The date  on which the record was approved.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Approved By</entry>
                           <entry>The name of the approver.</entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>FORECAST DETAILS</uicontrol> page displays the following non-editable fields:<table colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <tgroup cols="2">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="30%"/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="70%"/>
                     <thead>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Column Name</entry>
                           <entry>Description</entry>
                        </row>
                     </thead>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Name</entry>
                           <entry>Name of the forecast is displayed.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Start Date</entry>
                           <entry>The  start date of the forecast.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>End Date</entry>
                           <entry>The  end date of the forecast.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Duration </entry>
                           <entry>Based on the  start date and end date, the duration is displayed.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Curve</entry>
                           <entry>Displays the distribution curve that is applied to the   budget. </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Unit</entry>
                           <entry>The unit for the item as defined in the budget estimate.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Amount in $</entry>
                           <entry>Displays the total <uicontrol>Amount in $</uicontrol> for each item from the <uicontrol>CURRENT BUDGET ITEMS</uicontrol> page.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Remaining Amount in $</entry>
                           <entry>It is calculated as: Amount in $ - Sum of Amounts in Forecast<p>This helps the Project Manager understand if there is a overshoot or undershoot of the budget.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>&lt;&lt;Month Year&gt;&gt; </entry>
                           <entry>Displays  budget distribution  across  various months of the project. <p>You can toggle between the monthly or yearly view using the <uicontrol>Monthly View</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>Yearly View</uicontrol> toolbar options, respectively.<note> The default cost distribution, as   monthly or yearly, is configured in the  <uicontrol>Budget Management</uicontrol> page of the <uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol> module. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content">For more information, refer to <xref href="../../Administration/Functional_Configurations/CnfigBdgtMgmt.xml"/>
                                    </ph>
                                 </note>
                              </p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
